## 5. Prisma Schema â€” Data Model

```
User        id (uuid PK), email (unique), passwordHash, createdAt
Board       id (uuid PK), name, ownerId (FKâ†’User), createdAt
Task        id (uuid PK), title, description?, status (TaskStatus), priority (Priority), boardId (FKâ†’Board), ownerId (FKâ†’User), createdAt, updatedAt
AuditLog    id (uuid PK), userId (FKâ†’User), action (String), entity (String), entityId (String), createdAt
```

Enums:
- `TaskStatus`: `TODO | IN_PROGRESS | REVIEW | DONE`
- `Priority`: `LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH`

All relations use `onDelete: Cascade`. All primary keys are UUIDs.

AuditLog is written **by the Worker only** â€” the API never writes to AuditLog directly.

